3233 // a stable workload, the number of deletion entries should be roughly
3234 // equal to the number of non-deletion entries. If we compensate the
3235 // size of deletion entries in a stable workload, the deletion
3236 // compensation logic might introduce unwanted effet which changes the
3237 // shape of LSM tree.

3242 file_meta->num_entries) *

4470 };

4482 sstableKeyCompare(user_cmp, cur_limit, next_start) == 0;
4483 end_index -= is_overlapping;
4484 }
4485 }
4486 }

4493 *next_smallest = nullptr;
4494 }
4495 return;
4496 }

4502 *file_index = start_index;
4503 }
4504

4507 inputs->push_back(files_[level][i]);
4508 }
4509

4511 // Provide the next key outside the range covered by inputs
4512 if (end_index < static_cast<int>(files_[level].size())) {
4513 **next_smallest = files_[level][end_index]->smallest;
4514 } else {
4515 *next_smallest = nullptr;
4516 }
